      if (question.includes('forecast accuracy') || question.includes('how accurate') || question.includes('forecast reliable')) {
        return `**Forecast Accuracy Explained** 📊

**Accuracy by Timeframe:**

**Today (0-12 hours):**
🎯 95-99% accurate
• Most reliable
• Minor adjustments only
• Great for planning

**Tomorrow (12-36 hours):**
🎯 85-90% accurate
• Very reliable
• Temperature within 2-3°C
• Precipitation 80% reliable

**2-3 Days Ahead:**
🎯 75-85% accurate
• Generally reliable
• Temperature within 3-4°C
• Conditions mostly correct

**4-7 Days Ahead:**
🎯 60-75% accurate
• Trends reliable
• Specific details less certain
• Good for general planning

**8-14 Days Ahead:**
🎯 50-60% accurate
• General trends only
• Specific forecasts unreliable
• Climate averages more useful

**Why Accuracy Decreases:**
1. 🌪️ Atmosphere is chaotic
2. 🦋 "Butterfly effect" compounds
3. 📊 Model limitations
4. 🌐 Limited data points
5. ⏰ More time = more uncertainty

**Most Accurate Predictions:**
✅ Temperature trends
✅ Pressure systems
✅ Large-scale patterns
✅ Seasonal changes

**Least Accurate:**
❌ Exact rain start time
❌ Microclimate details
❌ Sudden severe weather
❌ Long-range specifics

**Pro Tips:**
💡 Check forecasts daily
💡 Look at trends, not just numbers
💡 Use multiple sources
💡 Understand confidence levels
💡 Have backup plans!

**Remember:**
Weather is dynamic - forecasts are predictions, not guarantees! 🌤️`;
